Requirements - KursarScript (KSPL)
üèóÔ∏è System Requirements
Minimum Requirements
Python: 3.7 or higher

RAM: 512MB minimum, 1GB recommended

Disk Space: 50MB free space

OS: Windows 10+, macOS 10.14+, or Linux (Ubuntu 18.04+, Fedora 30+, etc.)

Recommended for VR Development
RAM: 4GB or more

GPU: Any modern graphics card with VR support (optional)

Storage: 200MB for development projects

Python Packages: As specified below

üì¶ Python Package Dependencies
Core Dependencies (Automatically installed)
These are required for basic KursarScript functionality:

bash

Copy

Download
# KursarScript will automatically install these:
- No external dependencies for core interpreter
- Pure Python implementation
Optional Dependencies (Install as needed)
For Virtual Reality Integration
bash

Copy

Download
# Enhanced VR features
pip install pygame>=2.0.0        # For 2D VR simulation
pip install numpy>=1.21.0        # For mathematical operations in VR space
For Advanced Graphics
bash

Copy

Download
# 3D visualization support
pip install pyglet>=1.5.0        # For 3D graphics and windowing
pip install pyrr>=0.10.0         # For 3D mathematics
For Web Integration
bash

Copy

Download
# Web-based VR environments
pip install flask>=2.0.0         # For web server integration
pip install websockets>=10.0     # For real-time WebSocket communication
Development Dependencies
bash

Copy

Download
# For contributing to KursarScript development
pip install pytest>=6.0.0        # Testing framework
pip install black>=21.0.0        # Code formatting
pip install flake8>=4.0.0        # Code linting
pip install mypy>=0.900          # Type checking
üéÆ VR Environment Requirements
For Native VR Integration
VR Headset: Optional - HTC Vive, Oculus Rift, or compatible

SteamVR: Version 1.0 or higher (for headset integration)

VR Runtime: OpenXR compatible runtime

For Desktop/Simulation Mode
Display: 1024x768 minimum resolution

Input: Mouse and keyboard (game controllers optional)

Audio: Optional - for immersive experiences

üöÄ Quick Installation
Basic Installation
bash

Copy

Download
# Install KursarScript core
pip install kursarscript

# Verify installation
kursarscript --version
Full Installation (All Features)
bash

Copy

Download
# Install with all optional dependencies
pip install "kursarscript[full]"

# Or install individually
pip install kursarscript          # Core language
pip install kursarscript-vr       # VR extensions
pip install kursarscript-web      # Web integration
Development Installation
bash

Copy

Download
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/kursarscript.git
cd kursarscript

# Install in development mode
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run tests
pytest tests/
üîß Platform-Specific Notes
Windows
Python 3.7+ from Microsoft Store or python.org

Ensure Python is added to PATH

Administrator rights not required

macOS
Python 3.7+ via Homebrew: brew install python

May need to install command line tools: xcode-select --install

Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)
bash

Copy

Download
# Install Python 3.8+
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3.8 python3-pip

# Install KursarScript
pip3 install kursarscript
Linux (Fedora/RHEL)
bash

Copy

Download
# Install Python 3.8+
sudo dnf install python3.8 python3-pip

# Install KursarScript
pip3 install kursarscript
